Robert L. DUNN, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 9128. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Oct. 22, 1942. John W. Hilldrop, of Nashville, Tenn., for appellant. Horace Frierson, Jr., U. S. Atty., of Nashville, Tenn., for appellee.

Before HICKS, ALLEN, and HAMILTON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

This cause was heard on the transcript of the record and brief of appellant, oral argument having been waived; and it appearing to the court that there is no reversible error upon the record, it is ordered and adjudged that the judgment appealed from be, and the same is in all things, affirmed.
